ecosim

Class MasterVariables

  • java.lang.Object
    • ecosim.MasterVariables

  • public class MasterVariables
extends java.lang.Object
    This class holds the master variables that may need to be changed later into the project, so that the programmer will not have to go through each class and change them manually.
    Author:
    Andrew Warner & Jason Wood

    • Method Detail

      • getSortPercentage

        public int getSortPercentage()
        Returns the percentage to start sorting at, where 2 starts at 1.5x, 1 starts at 2x, etc (see FredOutVal documentation).
        Returns:
        The sort percentage.

      • setSortPercentage

        public void setSortPercentage(int newVal)
        Set the starting percentage for comparison, the default is 2, ie, values are sorted based on their 1.5x values, then by their 2x values, then by 5x. A value of 3 here would mean that output values are sorted instead by their 1.25x values, then by 1.5x, then by 2x, etc. pre - newVal is between 2 and 5. post - The new value is stored in sortPercentage.
        Parameters:
        newVal - The new value to be stored in sortPercentage.
